  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Information released regarding the provision of a plane for the President to go to the Maldives",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Air Force said that the President was granted a flight to the Maldives with the permission of the Ministry of Defense under the authority of the Executive President.",
        "There were reports in the media and various social media regarding the departure of the President from the country early this morning via the Katunayake Airport to Malatipu by a Sri Lankan Air Force aircraft.",
        "Pursuant to the powers vested in the Executive President in the Constitution of Sri Lanka and at the request of the present Government, a flight has been provided by the Air Force on 13 July 2022 for the President and his wife and two bodyguards to travel to the Maldives at the Katunayake International Airport with the full approval of the Ministry of Defence, subject to all immigration, customs and other laws. Sri Lankan Air Force said."
      ],
